The paper deals with the problem of automatic segmentation of retinal and choroidal layers in OCT images, which is a common task in computer vision (CV) and medical imaging (MM) research. The proposed method involves the use of deep neural networks (NN) and uncertainty-guided domain alignment techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories of CV, machine learning (LG), artificial intelligence (AI), multimedia (MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (NE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
